<br>
If I understand the UK Tax License system correctly... It is a Government mandated fee that goes to pay for programming on BBC (And maybe on other channels as well?)<br>
<br>
In Short, It is a Tax.<br>
<br>
I suppose it is probably just as unbiased as NPR (National Public Radio) here in the states...  Don't think that Government funding makes it any less biased.<br>
<br>
Remember, EVERYONE is biased, every media outlet is biased. Its just a matter of identifying the biases, and recognizign your own. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukintire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kintire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/02 3:41:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4495.topic&index=134>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Axis of Evil&quot;</span><hr size=1> The BBC is a corporation with it's own structure, and independent director general. It is funded by the Crown via the license fee which is payable by anyone who owns a television... which is pretty much everybody these days. The BBC runs various TV and Radio stations.<br>
<br>
Although Crown funded, the government of the day has no power of promotion or appointment within the BBC, and it makes strenuous efforts to avoid bias, giving equal airtime to spokesmen from both parties and so on. I have found no evidence of bias across the BBC at all, although individual presenters and editors have their own opinions of course. Still, the News section is uncredulous and has an excellent reputation for objectivity. I believe its about as good as you can get. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showPrevMessage?topicID=4495.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showNextMessage?topicID=4495.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4495.topic&index=134><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.emailToFriend?topicID=4495.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.threadControl?topicID=4495.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4495.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4495.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </